.TH LPF-EBPF 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.3.0" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-ebpf \- compile, load, observe, and roll back the eBPF datapath
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf ebpf <show|load|observe|rollback> [\-\-observed <path>|\-\-live] [\-\-run] <policy>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Compile policy into an eBPF datapath image of typed BPF maps and an XDP/TC/cgroup/LSM attach plan, then load, observe, or roll it back.
show renders the map image; load emits or runs the bpftool loader; observe reads live per\-rule counters; rollback flips the active version map atomically.
Identity\-aware policy is expressed with reserved table names (cgroup_*, proc_*, dns_*) referenced from rules.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-\-run
execute the generated bpftool loader instead of printing it
.TP
\-\-observed <path>
read an observed ebpf image from a file or \- for stdin
.TP
\-\-live
read observed counters from the host via bpftool
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf ebpf show fixtures/policies/basic.lpf
lpf ebpf load \-\-run /etc/lpf.conf
lpf ebpf observe \-\-live
lpf ebpf rollback
.SH FILES
/sys/fs/bpf/lpf
/var/lib/lpf/ebpf
.SH SAFETY NOTES
eBPF apply requires CAP_BPF/CAP_NET_ADMIN and a BTF\-capable kernel.
Loader runs in maps\-only mode unless LPF_BPF_OBJECT points to a verified CO\-RE object.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf\-plan(8), lpf\-diff(8), lpf\-apply(8)
